> Does planning, cooking, and packing kids' lunches and snacks feel like your part-time
> (or full-time) job? We feel you, and we're here to help. This 20-minute lunch is
> the perfect make-ahead lunchbox time-saver: a kid-approved pepperoni pizza-style
> quesadilla complete with carrot sticks and apple and pear slices. But it'll be
> snacktime before you know it! Serve up irresistible cinnamon-sugar coated pretzel
> nuggets with sweet cream cheese icing. That's right: We're thinking outside the lunchbox!

== Kids' Pepperoni Pizza-dillas ==

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @apple{1}. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce}
into sticks (like fries; ours were 3 inches long and 1⁄3 inch thick). Halve, core,
and thinly slice @pear{1}.

Place @flour tortillas{6} on a clean #work surface{}.

Evenly spread one half of each tortilla with @marinara cup{2.5%ounce}. Top with as
much @pepperoni{3.5%ounce} as you like, then sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1%cup}.

Fold tortillas in half to create pizza-dillas.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably
#nonstick pan{} over medium heat. Add pizza-dillas and cook until tortillas are
browned and cheese melts, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. (For 6 servings, you may need to
work in batches, using a large drizzle of oil for each batch.) Transfer to a
#cutting board{}.

To serve: Halve pizza-dillas. Divide between plates and serve with apple slices,
carrot sticks, and pear slices.

To stash: Let pizza-dillas cool completely before halving. Refrigerate
pizza-dillas, apple slices, carrot sticks, and pear slices in separate
#airtight containers{} and pack as desired!

== Cinnamon-Sugar Pretzel Nuggets with Cream Cheese Icing ==

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 350 degrees.

Place @butter{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 6 servings) in a large
#microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until butter melts, ~{30-45%seconds}. Add
@white sugar{2%teaspoon} and @cinnamon{1/2%teaspoon} (3 tsp white sugar and ¾ tsp
cinnamon for 6); whisk to combine.

Add @pretzel bites{1} to bowl with cinnamon-sugar butter; toss to evenly coat.

Arrange coated pretzel bites in a single layer on a #baking sheet{} (drizzle any
remaining cinnamon-sugar butter over top). Bake on middle rack until lightly glazed
and warmed through, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place @cream cheese{2%tablespoon} in a medium
#microwave-safe bowl{} (use a second large bowl for 6 servings); cover with
#plastic wrap{}. Microwave until softened, about ~{30%seconds}. Add @yogurt{6%tablespoon}
and @powdered sugar{2%ounce}; whisk until smooth.

Serve cinnamon-sugar pretzel bites with cream cheese icing on the side for dipping.